cs.NI, cs.RO, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.CV

The paper presents a drone-based solution that utilizes machine learning techniques to locate missing people through their mobile phones in disaster scenarios. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as the paper focuses on the development of a mobile network solution. The paper also involves the use of autonomous drones, which falls under the category of cs.RO (Robotics). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques, which could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of cameras for human/computer vision, which could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Finally, the paper discusses the challenges of finding missing persons in disaster scenarios, which could be categorized under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
